---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const pageTitle = 'Nathan Kisiel';
---

<BaseLayout {pageTitle}>
  <!-- HOME -->
  <section id="home" class="home-hero">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h1 class="home-hero__title">Nathan Kisiel</h1>

      <p class="home-hero__blurb">
        Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Proin feugiat porta nulla,
        quis vehicula nisi porttitor eget. Fusce eget vehicula nisl, at molestie magna.
        Morbi lacinia dui eget libero placerat semper.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ABOUT -->
  <section id="about" class="about">
    <div class="section-inner about__inner">
      <h2 class="about__title">About Me</h2>

      <div class="about__image-wrap">
        <img
          class="about__image"
          src="/img/about pic.png"
          alt="Abstract mountains illustration"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="about__text">
        <p>
          I’m a rising senior at Allegheny College pursuing a B.S. in Mathematics with a focus on actuarial science. 
          I’m actively preparing for actuarial certification while completing my undergraduate studies and have successfully 
          passed the Society of Actuaries Exam P and Exam FM.
        </p>

        <p>
          My academic interests center on probability, financial mathematics, and risk modeling, and I enjoy applying quantitative theory to real-world financial and insurance problems. 
          Through coursework and independent projects, I’ve developed a strong foundation in analytical thinking, problem-solving, and mathematical modeling.
        </p>

        <p>
          I’m currently seeking opportunities to apply my skills in an actuarial or analytical role where I can 
          continue learning, contribute meaningfully, and grow within the profession.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ACTUARY EXAMS -->
<section id="exams" class="exams">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <h2 class="exams__title">Actuary Exams</h2>

    <div class="exams__grid">
      <!-- Exam P -->
      <article class="exam-card">
        <div class="exam-card__top">
          <h3 class="exam-card__title">Exam P — Probability</h3>
          <span class="exam-card__status exam-card__status--passed">Passed</span>
        </div>

        <p class="exam-card__text">
          Through Society of Actuaries Exam P, I developed a strong foundation in probability theory and its application to modeling uncertainty. I learned how to work with discrete and continuous random variables, common probability distributions, and key measures such as expected value, variance, and covariance.
          In addition, I gained experience analyzing stochastic processes and understanding how randomness evolves over time, which is essential for modeling real-world risk. 
        </p>

        <div class="exam-tags">
          <span class="exam-tag">Probability Theory</span>
          <span class="exam-tag">Statistical Modeling</span>
          <span class="exam-tag">Quantitative Analysis</span>
          <span class="exam-tag">Expected Value & Variance Analysis</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Exam FM -->
      <article class="exam-card">
        <div class="exam-card__top">
          <h3 class="exam-card__title">Exam FM — Financial Mathematics</h3>
          <span class="exam-card__status exam-card__status--passed">Passed</span>
        </div>

        <p class="exam-card__text">
          Exam FM taught me the core principles of financial mathematics and the time value of money. I gained experience calculating present and future values of cash flows and working with annuities, loans, amortization schedules, and bonds. I also learned how interest rates and compounding affect long-term financial obligations and how to evaluate cash flows using yield rates.
          Beyond these fundamentals, I developed a deeper understanding of how financial instruments are structured and valued in practice. 
        </p>

        <div class="exam-tags">
          <span class="exam-tag">Interest Theory</span>
          <span class="exam-tag">Duration & Convexity</span>
          <span class="exam-tag">Financial Modeling</span>
          <span class="exam-tag">Bond Pricing & Yield Analysis</span>
          <span class="exam-tag">Risk & Return Concepts</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Exam SRM -->
      <article class="exam-card">
        <div class="exam-card__top">
          <h3 class="exam-card__title">Exam SRM — Statistics for Risk Modeling</h3>
          <span class="exam-card__status exam-card__status--progress">In Progress</span>
        </div>

        <p class="exam-card__text">
          Through Exam SRM, I developed a strong foundation in statistical learning and data-driven modeling. I learned how to apply regression techniques, including linear and logistic regression, to analyze relationships between variables and make predictions. The exam introduced key concepts in model selection, such as overfitting, bias-variance tradeoff, and cross-validation, which helped me understand how to build models that generalize well to new data. 
        </p>

        <div class="exam-tags">
          <span class="exam-tag">Linear & Logistic Regression</span>
          <span class="exam-tag">Data Analysis & Interpretation</span>
          <span class="exam-tag">Bias-Variance Tradeoff</span>
          <span class="exam-tag">Statistical Learning & Predictive Modeling</span>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

  <!-- PROJECTS -->
<section id="projects" class="projects">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <h2 class="projects__title">Projects</h2>

    <div class="projects__grid">

      <article class="project-card">
        <img class="project-card__img" src="/img/probability.png" alt="Project placeholder" />
        <h3 class="project-card__title">Probability Distribution</h3>
        <p class="project-card__text">
          Through my probability research project, I explored advanced mathematical concepts by studying a specialized function and its applications within probability theory. I conducted research using mathematical journals and textbooks, which strengthened my ability to engage with technical literature and independently learn material.
          A key focus of the project was analyzing the relationship between hypergeometric series and probability distributions.
        </p>

        <div class="project-skills">
          <h4 class="project-skills__title">Skills Used</h4>
          <ul class="project-skills__list">
            <li>Advanced math analysis</li>
            <li>Probability modeling</li>
            <li>Mathmatical Derivations</li>
            <li>Presentation skills</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>


      <article class="project-card">
        <img class="project-card__img" src="/img/datascience.png" alt="Project placeholder" />
        <h3 class="project-card__title">Data Analysis</h3>
        <p class="project-card__text">
          Through my data science project, I analyzed the relationship between caffeine consumption and hours of sleep using regression techniques. Utilizing the RStudio environment and the R programming language, I collected, cleaned, and analyzed data to identify trends and quantify relationships between variables.
          I applied regression models to examine how caffeine intake may impact sleep duration, interpreting coefficients, statistical significance, and overall model fit.
        </p>

        <div class="project-skills">
          <h4 class="project-skills__title">Skills Used</h4>
          <ul class="project-skills__list">
            <li>Data collection</li>
            <li>Data cleaning</li>
            <li>Regression analysis</li>
            <li>R programming</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>


      <article class="project-card">
        <img class="project-card__img" src="/img/seniorproject.png" alt="Project placeholder" />
        <h3 class="project-card__title">Senior Project</h3>
        <p class="project-card__text">
          Through my senior project in mathematics, I explored the relationship between financial modeling, interest theory, and market structure. I focused on how concepts such as present and future value, discounting, and compounding can be used to analyze long-term financial outcomes and decision-making.
          This project allowed me to apply theoretical principles from actuarial science to more complex, real-world scenarios involving cash flow valuation and economic behavior.
        </p>

        <div class="project-skills">
          <h4 class="project-skills__title">Skills Used</h4>
          <ul class="project-skills__list">
            <li>Financial Mathematics</li>
            <li>Discounted Cash Flow Analysis</li>
            <li>Present & Future Value Modeling</li>
            <li>Quantitative Economic Modeling</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

  <!-- EXPERIENCE -->
<section id="experience" class="experience">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <h2 class="experience__title">Experience</h2>

    <div class="experience__grid">

      <article class="experience-card">
        <h3 class="experience-card__title">Student Relationship Banker</h3>
        <p class="experience-card__meta">First National Bank</p>
        <p class="experience-card__text">
          Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Proin feugiat porta nulla,
          quis vehicula nisi porttitor eget. Fusce eget vehicula nisl, at molestie magna.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="experience-card">
        <h3 class="experience-card__title">IT Help Desk</h3>
        <p class="experience-card__meta">Allegheny College</p>
        <p class="experience-card__text">
          Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Proin feugiat porta nulla,
          quis vehicula nisi porttitor eget. Fusce eget vehicula nisl, at molestie magna.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="experience-card">
        <h3 class="experience-card__title">Supervisor</h3>
        <p class="experience-card__meta">Amusement Park</p>
        <p class="experience-card__text">
          Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Proin feugiat porta nulla,
          quis vehicula nisi porttitor eget. Fusce eget vehicula nisl, at molestie magna.
        </p>
